DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Interval");
$b = random(1,8);
$answer= Interval("[$b,Inf)");
$f= Formula("sqrt(x-$b)");


BEGIN_PGML

Let [`f(x)`] =  [`[$f]`].   Use [@ helpLink("interval notation") @]*  to indicate where [`f(x)`] is continuous.

Domain of continuity:[___________]{$answer}{15}

END_PGML

$showHint=3;
BEGIN_PGML_HINT
The domain of a square root function is the set of all real numbers for which the function is defined. Therefore, the expression [`x`]-[$b] inside the square root [` \sqrt{} `] must not be negative.
END_PGML_HINT


BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The square root function is continuous on its domain. So [`x`]-[$b] >= 0. Thus [`x >=`] [$b] which is [`[$answer]`] in interval notation.
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();